The Wuhan Municipal Health Commission, on 31 December, made a statement to the population and informed WHO.
Sufficient cases of pneumonia of unknown origin had already been reported to the Wuhan health authorities to generate an investigation in early January. During the first stages of the outbreak, the number of cases doubled every seven and a half days, approximately.
In early and mid-January 2020, the virus spread through other provinces of China, facilitated by the migration of the new Chinese year and the fact that Wuhan is a transport center, besides a main point of rail connection.
