It is suspected that Shincheonji devotees who visited Daegu from Wuhan were the origin of the outbreak.
On 22 February, between the 9,336 church followers, 1,261, or about 13% of them, reported having symptoms. South Korea declared maximum alert level on 23 February 2020.
